<item>
            <title>[FLINK-3718] Add Option For Completely Async Backup in RocksDB State Backend</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-3718</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Right now, the snapshotting for RocksDB has a synchronous part where a backup of the RocksDB database is drawn and an asynchronous part where this backup is written to HDFS.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should add an option that uses the snapshot feature of RocksDB to get an iterator over all keys at a set point in time. The iterator can be used to store everything to HDFS. Normal operation can continue while we store the keys. This makes the snapshot completely asynchronous.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
